    <string name="about_activity_title">About</string>
    <string name="about_heading_features">Features</string>
    <string name="about_features_content">
        <ul>
            <li>Solve Terminals with by just tapping on words.\n</li>
            <li>Undo lets you correct mistakes without restarting.\n</li>
            <li>Restart the solver if you need to.\n</li>
            <li>Stat tracking.\n</li>
            <li>On devices with Android 7.1, use built in app shortcuts to view stats or solve a terminal.\n</li>
        </ul>
    </string>

    <string name="about_heading_how_it_works">How to Use</string>
    <string name="about_how_it_works_content">
        <ol>
            <li>Click start and start typing the words into the input boxes. You can press done on the soft keybaord to quickly add new words.\n\n</li>
            <li>After all words have been given, tap next to proceed to the elimination screen. Make sure all the words are uppercase.\n\n</li>
            <li>Tap on the yellow words apply them as a filter. Give in the likeness that the terminal in Fallout 4 has given you for that word.\n\n</li>
            <li>Repeat until the solver is done. Green words are applied filters (words selected in the Terminal). Grey words are ones that are eliminated and cannot be the terminal password.\n\n</li>
        </ol>
    </string>

